.TH MYBLUETOOTH "1" "December 2025" "mybluetooth 202208131722-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mybluetooth \- Bluetooth device management script
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mybluetooth
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR] [\fI\,DEVICE\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mybluetooth
is a script for managing Bluetooth devices on Linux systems. It provides a command-line interface for discovering, pairing, connecting, and managing Bluetooth devices.
.PP
The script simplifies common Bluetooth operations and can also launch a graphical interface for more complex management tasks.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B gui
Open the graphical Bluetooth manager interface
.TP
.B discover [on|off]
Turn Bluetooth discovery mode on or off
.TP
.B search
Search for nearby Bluetooth devices
.TP
.B status
Display current Bluetooth adapter status
.TP
.B pair \fI\,DEVICE\/\fR
Pair with a Bluetooth device (specify device address)
.TP
.B unpair \fI\,DEVICE\/\fR
Remove/unpair a Bluetooth device
.TP
.B connect \fI\,DEVICE\/\fR
Connect to a paired Bluetooth device
.TP
.B disconnect \fI\,DEVICE\/\fR
Disconnect from a Bluetooth device
.TP
.B config \fI\,DEVICE\/\fR \fI\,NAME\/\fR
Create a configuration file for a device with a friendly name
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available commands
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B mybluetooth status
Check Bluetooth adapter status
.TP
.B mybluetooth search
Scan for nearby Bluetooth devices
.TP
.B mybluetooth pair AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF
Pair with device at specified address
.TP
.B mybluetooth connect AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF
Connect to a paired device
.TP
.B mybluetooth config AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF speaker
Create config for device with name "speaker"
.TP
.B mybluetooth gui
Open graphical Bluetooth manager
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/mybluetooth/settings.conf
User configuration file for mybluetooth preferences
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/mybluetooth/devices/
Directory storing device configurations
.TP
.B ~/.local/log/mybluetooth/
Log file directory for error tracking
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error or operation failed
.TP
.B 3
Required command not found
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Requires bluetoothctl or similar Bluetooth management tools
.IP \(bu 2
Device addresses are in XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX format
.IP \(bu 2
GUI mode requires blueman or similar graphical tool
.IP \(bu 2
Opens in a terminal if not already running in one
